10:23 AM Defendant Luis E Meza Juarez in court, in custody, with attorney Joseph James Dorlack.   Shawn N Woller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court conducts plea colloquy.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1,  Court finds defendant guilty.  Cases 15CM1049, 15CM1417 and 19CF940 dismissed and read in  to this matter.  Recommendations by the State.  Recommendations by the Defense.  Statement by defendant.

The Court Orders the Following:

Count 1:
Withheld Sentence (Credit for 150 days if revoked)

Term of Probation: 2 Years
Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No contact with victim from 19CF940, A.C.O.
-            While defendant is in custody there are no restrictions on contact with victim, Y.C.D.  When defendant is released there is to be no contact with victim, Y.C.D. unless she consents and the Agent agrees.
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No Use or Possession of CBD products;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctors prescription
-	Domestic Violence counseling.

COSTS:  $ 343.00

DNA Surcharge: $ 200.00

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation
